The paper discusses the use of machine learning to optimize the execution of computational jobs in HPC applications. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). However, given the focus on machine learning and optimization, cs.DC and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.SE, and cs.CE.
